<section id="slide-orgc805e54">
<h3 id="orgc805e54">Related techniques</h3>
<ul>
<li>Transactional analysis (Berne)</li>
<li>Psychodrama (Moreno)</li>
<li>Family sculptures (Satir)</li>
<li>Gestalt therapy (Perls)</li>
<li>Primal scream therapy (Janov)</li>
<li>Neuro-linguistic programming (Bandler/Grindler)</li>

</ul>

</section>
<section id="slide-org52608c3">
<h3 id="org52608c3">Model uses: see what is</h3>

<div class="figure">
<p><img src="./img/order.png" alt="order.png" width="400px" />
</p>
</div>

<ul>
<li>Overcome defensiveness</li>
<li>Establish/strengthen relationships</li>
<li>Reveal hidden truths or facts</li>

</ul>

</section>
<section id="slide-org8597b54">
<h3 id="org8597b54">Model assumptions</h3>

<div class="figure">
<p><img src="./img/pyramids.png" alt="pyramids.png" width="400px" />
</p>
</div>

<ul>
<li>System boundaries count<sup><a id="fnr.2" class="footref" href="#fn.2">2</a></sup></li>
<li>System belonging time counts<sup><a id="fnr.3" class="footref" href="#fn.3">3</a></sup></li>
<li>Older systems have precedence<sup><a id="fnr.4" class="footref" href="#fn.4">4</a></sup></li>
<li>Acknowledging what is counts<sup><a id="fnr.5" class="footref" href="#fn.5">5</a></sup></li>

</ul>

</section>
